# Artifacts Routing Policy

Non-release artifacts for this project live in the **`artifacts/`** directory, which is a
private git submodule pointing to `git@github.com:davechogan/mkc-inventory-artifacts.git`.

## Decision rule

- If a file is required for app runtime, build, or CI: keep it in the main repo.
- If a file is historical, investigative, environment-specific, or snapshot data: store it in `artifacts/`.

## Artifact mapping (required)

| Artifact type | Path in artifacts/ |
|---|---|
| Architecture plans, implementation specs | `artifacts/plans/` |
| Investigation notes, postmortems | `artifacts/plans/` |
| One-off helper scripts (non-runtime) | `artifacts/scripts/` |
| DB snapshots/backups (compressed) | `artifacts/db_snapshots/<YYYY-MM-DD>/` |
| Test seed DB (uncompressed, canonical) | `artifacts/db_snapshots/mkc_inventory_seed.db` |
| Exports (CSV/JSON), ad hoc reports | `artifacts/exports/` (gitignored — local use only) |
| Diagnostic logs | `artifacts/logs/` (gitignored — local use only) |
| Provenance/checksums/restore metadata | `artifacts/metadata/` |

## Submodule setup (first-time / new dev machine)

```bash
git submodule update --init
```

Requires access to `git@github.com:davechogan/mkc-inventory-artifacts.git` (private).
If you do not have access, the test suite falls back to `tests/fixtures/mkc_inventory_seed.db`.

## Committing artifacts alongside code

**Always use `scripts/commit.sh` instead of bare `git commit`.**
This commits any pending artifact changes to the submodule first, then commits
the updated submodule pointer and all main-repo changes together with the same message.

```bash
scripts/commit.sh "feat(reporting): add query rewriter and field coverage expansion"
```

## Required controls for DB snapshots

- Prefer compressed snapshots (`.gz`), not raw DB for dated backups.
- Include `SHA256SUMS.txt` for each snapshot batch.
- Include provenance metadata (`source repo`, `commit`, `timestamp`, `author`, `artifact list`).
- Never store secrets/credentials.

## Do not commit to the main repo

- `data/*.db`, backup DB snapshots, local logs, exported CSV/JSON artifacts.
- `tests/fixtures/mkc_inventory_seed.db` — canonical copy lives in `artifacts/`.
- Machine-local workspace files and worktree internals.
- Any artifact not needed to run, test, or release the app.
